A system for identification of command injection attacks, the system comprising:
 one or more devices connected to a network; 
 a non-transitory memory device, said non-transitory memory device having modules of instruction code stored thereon; 
 an execution platform executing executable products, said execution platform is connected to said one or more devices via said network, wherein said one or more devices are configured to provide execution commands to said execution platform; 
 one or more processors associated with said memory device, wherein at least one processor of said one or more processors is configured to execute the modules of instruction code, whereupon execution of said modules of instruction code said at least one processor is further configured to: 
 analyze execution commands provided to said execution platform to identify input provisioning events or execution events; 
 in response to identifying a potential input provisioning event, determine that an input of the potential input provisioning event includes a command separator and an executable product, wherein the input of the potential input provisioning event is received from said network, wherein the command separator is a character or combination of characters configured to separate between two commands; 
 in response to said determining that the input includes the command separator and the executable product, record a suspicious record event; 
 in response to identifying a potential execution event, determine that an execution command of the potential execution event correlates to the suspicious record event, wherein the execution command is configured to be executed by the potential execution event; 
 in response to said determining that the execution command correlates to the suspicious record event, flag the execution command as a command injection attack; and 
 perform a remedial action with respect to the flagged command injection attack prior to attempting to execute the execution command by said execution platform.

